title: Market Intelligence Analytics & Data Quality Senior Manager
description:
The Audit & Assurance Marketplace & Risk Intelligence group (Marketplace & Risk Intelligence) is a small team within Deloitte’s Audit practice responsible for creating cutting-edge web-based applications and actionable market intelligence for our audit practitioners and leadership. The team consists of highly skilled UI designers, researchers, data analysts and developers. The work we do is agile, exciting and is a valued contribution to our audit practice. Our work is critical to support leadership strategic decision-making and enable excellent client service and growth of our Audit and Assurance practice.

The Marketplace & Risk Intelligence team is looking for an experienced “Analytics & Data Quality Senior Manager”.
The Analytics & Data Quality Senior Manager will interact regularly with our technical teams, researchers, analytics professionals, external third-party data providers, and audit business leaders. He or she will be involved end-to-end from the acquisition of data to the effective use of data within web-based applications and within data analyses prepared for the audit practice. In addition, this position currently includes directly managing two data analysts.

The position will provide an excellent opportunity to build individual your network, develop relationships, increase exposure to audit leadership, and be a part of a team within a highly strategic focus area of the Audit Practice. You will be able to access premium data and leverage your intellectual curiosity to develop new insightful analyses that drive strategic decisions.

Work you'll do
Actively drives the creation of insightful analyses to help inform audit leadership decision making. Transforms data into insights that are relevant to the audit business’s strategic goals
Reviews the presentation of data in audit market intelligence applications and from an auditor’s/ business perspective, make recommendations for changes/improvements
Leads/manages/performs testing and reviews to ensure completeness and accuracy of data/content presented in analyses and applications
Develops sound data strategies and methodology. Determines appropriate statistical analysis techniques to use
Meet directly with third-party data providers. Collaborate with researchers, developers, designers and others on the Marketplace & Risk Intelligence team. Meet directly with audit leadership to understand business needs and present work/deliverables
Improve data quality through organizational, procedural and/or technological means. Develops and implements new processes to ensure ongoing data quality, accuracy and completeness in audit market intelligence applications and analyses
Participates in new application development projects. Helps to define business rules that determines the display of data in our websites, assists the product owner in writing test scripts that validates business rules, and performs detailed and rigorous testing to ensure data quality. Active contributor to project teams
Develops a deep understanding of the data available and applications in the Marketplace & Risk Intelligence portfolio
Assists in the assessment of acquiring new data sources. Provides input on and advocates for future initiatives/projects/tools
Demonstrates leadership skills in managing and coaching Market Intelligence data analyst(s). Sets project direction, provides coaching, guidance, and reviews work for quality, completeness and accuracy
Builds stakeholder trust and confidence through being responsive, and delivering work that is accurate, complete and reliable. Helps to build increased demand for analysis services and a data-driven culture
Manages compliance with internal Deloitte policies, technology controls, governance and procedures
Performs other job-related duties as assigned.

Qualifications:
Required:

Bachelor’s degree and/or Master’s degree in a related discipline such as Business Intelligence, Business Analytics, or Accounting.
7+ years of related experience

Preferred:
Experience in data management & data governance a plus
Audit background, understanding of Audit related data
Advanced Excel skills
Ability to perform extensive data analysis (comparing multiple datasets) using a variety of techniques, visualizations and tools – to uncover patterns, predictions or insights
Strong analytical skills and intellectual curiosity
Strong project management skills
Employs critical thinking, objective analysis and evaluation of an issue in order to form a judgment/opinion/recommendation
Ability to drive continuous data management quality (i.e. completeness, accuracy) through defined and governed principles
Ability to identify and mitigate data quality issues effectively
Proven ability to develop strong collaborative relationships with internal stakeholders
Detail oriented. Highly organized.
Curious and creative mindset – willing to explore and has a passion for quantitative analysis and problem solving
Be able to plan and lead projects to completion
Shows initiative, good judgment, and resourcefulness.
Ability to get up-to-speed quickly, work independently and demonstrate solid decision-making skills
Willing to be hands-on
Exceptional verbal, written and presentation communication skills
Ability to take discussions and open issues to closure by working with local and remote/virtual teams
Be able to collaborate and lead effectively with a multidisciplinary team - developers, designers, researchers, audit practitioners, managing directors, partners and firm leadership
Contributes to a positive team environment
Proven ability to handle multiple projects simultaneously
Ability to respond quickly to high-priority deadlines and easily adapt to change
Excellent people management skills
Consistent, demonstrated high performer

The team
Our audits are fueled by more than just technology – what really sets us apart are our insightful professionals, collaborative culture, and commitment to innovation and continuous improvement. Our audit professionals apply a streamlined, intelligent approach to the audit, enabled by innovative tools and technologies. Quality is our top priority, and by focusing on innovation, we continue to raise the bar on quality and deliver greater value to our clients. Learn more about Deloitte Audit.

How you’ll grow
At Deloitte, we believe in professional development and helping our people grow. We offer learning opportunities to help you sharpen your skills in addition to hands-on experience in the global, fast-changing business world. We support the development of leadership and technical skills through leading-edge learning development solutions. Explore Deloitte University, The Leadership Center.

Benefits
At Deloitte, we know that great people make a great organization. We value our people and offer employees a broad range of benefits. Learn more about what working at Deloitte can mean for you.
Deloitte’s culture
Our positive and supportive culture encourages our people to do their best work every day. We celebrate individuals by recognizing their uniqueness and offering them the flexibility to make daily choices that can help them to be healthy, centered, confident, and aware. We offer well-being programs and are continuously looking for new ways to maintain a culture where our people excel and lead healthy, happy lives. Learn more about Life at Deloitte.

Corporate citizenship
Deloitte is led by a purpose: to make an impact that matters. This purpose defines who we are and extends to relationships with our clients, our people and our communities. We believe that business has the power to inspire and transform. We focus on education, giving, skill-based volunteerism, and leadership to help drive positive social impact in our communities. Learn more about Deloitte’s impact on the world.

Recruiter tips
We want job seekers exploring opportunities at Deloitte to feel prepared and confident. To help you with your interview, we suggest that you do your research: know some background about the organization and the business area you’re applying to. We also suggest that you brush up on your interviewing skills and practice discussing your experience and job history with a family member, friend, or mentor. Check out recruiting tips from Deloitte professionals.

title: Senior Data Intelligence Analyst
description:
Grow your career at Cedars-Sinai!

title: Director, Predictive Analytics
description:
Reporting to the Chief Financial Officer, interprets, analyzes an provides predictive modeling of university metrics including retention, placement, tuition and scholarships, graduation rates, student learning, and other relevant academic success factors to be used for decision making related to enhancing student outcomes and academic excellence.

Conducts research to determine best approach to collect required data. Supervises the collection, analysis, and rigor of data for use by the organization. Provides data analysis, interpretation, and preparation of reports. Provides information and analytic support to the University’s decision makers, and prompts activities to improve student persistence and academic success.

The ideal candidate is a graduate from a four-year college or university, including or supplemented by advanced understanding and applications of statistics, data mining, programming and data visualization is required. Graduate study in computer science, economics, mathematics, statistics, or engineering is highly desired. Three years of working experience in technical research, statistical work in the collection, compilation, and analysis of student, faculty, class, enrollment and financial planning data, data warehousing and higher education business intelligence. Five years of progressively responsible professional full-time experience in higher education Institutional Research or Data Science or Analytical Studies.

Demonstrated work experience in Institutional research in higher education including interpretation and presentation of student, faculty, class, enrollment and financial planning data is highly desired. Demonstrated working experience of SQL/PLSQL programming, CVUE, and Python Pandas and Scikit-Learn will be given due consideration. Candidates must also have a minimum three years of progressive responsibility in machine learning and deep learning using Python.

Three years of working experience leading and supervising a team of at least two data analysts. The supervisory experience requires recruiting, evaluating, coaching and optimizing talents and staff in a strong statistical, analytic, data management, and reporting and data visualization line of work.

Candidates must have working knowledge in the following:
Expert working knowledge in SQL.
Expert working knowledge in Python with mastery in all of the following:
Pandas and Numpy
Scikit-Learn
Matplotlib
Expert working knowledge in one of the following:
Plotly or Dash
Expert working knowledge in Jupyter Notebook from writing codes to presenting a complete analysis.
Expert working knowledge in Institutional Research in Higher Education. This must include complete understanding of varying working definitions as well as mastery in extracting and preparing data to be machine-learn-ready in all of the following research areas:
Student success metrics including:
Retention rates
Graduation rates
Pre-licensure board passage rates
Job placement rates
Student admission data
Student classes/courses data
Student term by term academic performance data
Faculty data
Enrollment planning data
Student assessment data
Expert working knowledge in deploying machine learning or predictive models in production environment for the frontline staff
The position requires a minimum of 5 years of progressively responsible professional full-time experience in higher education Institutional Research or Data Science or Analytical Studies.
Ability to develop metrics, measurements, templates and tools for continual improvement tracking and monitoring of key indicators for areas of responsibility that facilitate the process of research within a culture of “management by evidence”, decisions based on data.
Experience leading analytical teams, including cross functional business and technology teams.
Experience leading teams building analytical applications/products.
Ability to oversee execution of data and analytics roadmap, including establishing individual projects for delivery.

title: Director, Managed Care Analytics - REMOTE
description:
We are hospitals and affiliated medical groups, working closely together for the benefit of every person who comes to us for care. We build comprehensive networks of quality healthcare services that are designed to offer our patients highly coordinated, personalized care and help them live healthier lives. Through collaboration, we strive to provide all of our patients and medical group members with the quality, affordable healthcare they need and deserve.
The Director of Analytics for Managed Care will provide managed care business line leadership, direction, decision-making and oversight for CRC’s data management, analytics, and reporting needs. Leads and develops a team that will be responsible for the development of reporting for executive level management, and will be responsible for the timely and accurate preparation of summary and detail models used to support negotiations, the financial and analytical analysis of all managed care contracts including comparing payers payments to contracted rates, and comparison to like payers and governmental payers such as Medicare and Medicaid. Oversees local CRC analysts and provides direction. Oversees all physician, ancillary, small payer, and single case agreement analyses. Performs research on managed care and governmental payers as directed.
Job Responsibilities/Duties
Coordinates/conducts all phases of development of business intelligence for CRC. Demonstrates in depth knowledge of the Managed Care function. Functions as a super user of assigned data application(s) and reporting(s).Serves as an internal expert with respect to data understanding, interpretation, and accuracy.
Lead the development and manipulation of large data set and analyzes the performance of all managed care contracts/negotiations. Ensures timely and accurate financial and analytical analysis of assigned managed care contracts to support payer negotiations. Measures contract performance against financial and administrative goals and objectives for revenue, claims processing, eligibility verification, medical management, and dispute resolution. Generates and analyze market trends and conducts market research for use in the development of existing and future managed care programs and contract negotiations. Utilizes systems that will support Department and senior financial management review of contractual performance and the impact of new/proposed rates and terms. Maintains oversight of highly complex negotiation models in Microsoft Excel, Access and/or other application and to ensure that all applicable financial information flows seamlessly into a main summary.
Leads the development and manipulation of large data sets as well as the analysis of managed care data. Trends changes to service lines and suggests opportunities for revenue growth. Provides analytical review of models, identifying trends, risks, opportunities, and goals. Completes forecasting and modeling for Alternative Payment Methods and bundled payments. Forecasts and models changes to payer policies, CPT changes, Fee Schedule changes, Grouper Changes, DRG Conversions, New Services and other impacts to the contract as needed. Notify appropriate levels of management of these changes. Utilizes expertise to suggest improvements and report enhancements that will facilitate and/or provide new or better insight into the review process.
Provides critical support and leadership in implementing key planning and analysis tools to aid operational decision-making, and achievement of key performance indicators for the CRC team. Implements and maintain a contract management system which estimates the net revenue of all contracts and government payers.
Communicates effectively within/between departments to ensure prompt and proper information exchanges and issue resolution. Serves as a leader and problem solver to staff within the department and across the organization. Mentors and trains team members in critical thinking and complex analytical modeling. Delegates appropriately, providing adequate direction and follow up. Resolves escalated issues arising from operations. Maintains a visible presence on interdisciplinary committees and key work groups.
Provides support for contract negotiations for the VP, Managed Care Contracting and will lead assigned negotiations for certain physician, ancillary and small payer contracts as well as single case agreements as assigned.
Qualifications
Minimum Education: Bachelor’s Degree in Business, Healthcare or related discipline or equivalent experience. Master’s Degree preferred.
Minimum Experience: Ten (10) prior experience in Managed Care/Healthcare, including at least 2 years in a leadership role. Ability to manipulate large amounts of data by having exceptional Access and Excel skills. Excellent writing and verbal communications skills in English. Excellent process and project management skills required including the ability to manage a significant volume of projects with exercise of good triage and judgment skills. Experience translating business needs into data models and predictive algorithms analytics. In-depth background in Managed Care Systems Development and Project Management. Strong analytical and advanced computer skills including the ability to import/export from numerous source systems and merge/compare data. Ability to focus on data accuracy and reproducibility, including internal controls and quality checks when running analytic reports. Excellent understanding of related policies and regulations to perform analysis and provide recommendations to management.
Req. Certification/Licensure: None.
Employee Value Proposition
Prospect Medical Holdings, Inc., is guided by a diverse and highly experienced leadership core. This group maintains the vision that has made Prospect a needed difference-maker in the lives of so many patients today, and many executives contribute to our continued efforts. As a member of our highly effective team of professionals you will receive:
Company 401K
Medical, dental, vision insurance
Paid time-off
Life insurance
Prospect Medical Systems has a zero-tolerance policy regarding the use of drugs and alcohol. Our Company is committed to maintaining a productive, drug free workplace that keeps employees and patients safe from harm. For this reason, we require applicants to pass a screening for drug use as a condition of employment. This includes: alcohol, marijuana, cocaine, opiates and methamphetamines.

title: Senior Analyst, Data Intelligence
description:
To get the best candidate experience, please consider applying for a maximum of 3 roles within 12 months to ensure you are not duplicating efforts.
Job Category
Products and Technology
Job Details
Department Overview - Data Intelligence
The Data Intelligence (DI) team is made up of data scientists, data engineers, visualization developers, and analysts who are dedicated to driving product strategy with data-driven insights. The DI team works with executives, product managers, designers, developers, user researchers, marketers, and sales strategy team members across all Cloud businesses to discover new opportunities for growth and optimization, experiment with data, drive adoption, and provide actionable insights that impact product strategy.

Role Description:
The Senior Analyst of the Data Intelligence team will report to the Senior Director of Strategy and Growth of the Data Intelligence team and will help shape Salesforce products with data-driven decisions and data products. This candidate will be responsible for working in a collaborative, cross-functional environment to deliver insights based on data, recommend improvements, and conduct product adoption tests (A/B, Multivariate).
This role requires expert-level experience driving adoption growth and technical expertise in adoption tools, data mining, and visualization. This role also requires advanced communication skills to collaborate effectively in a large, matrixed environment, and a high level of comfort with public speaking and executive presentations.

Responsibilities
Develop quantitative analysis, ad hoc reports, and models to support product decision-making.
Translate data insights into actions and recommendations that will drive product adoption, customer satisfaction, and investment decisions.
Partner with product leaders to understand business requirements, product direction, roadmaps, key metrics, and growth goals.
Identify, acquire, consolidate and manipulate data features from multiple sources including product log files, dimensional data, Salesforce objects, and external data sources to develop models and analyses, produce insights that will guide product strategy and investment decisions.
Partner with the data engineering team and product engineering team to instrument, acquire, develop and structure data assets that are critical to measuring the products.
Create KPIs based on knowledge of the Salesforce business, growth drivers, and industry benchmarks.
Design and implement reporting dashboards that track key metrics and performance trends, and provide actionable insights to product leadership.
Create visualizations, presentations, and executive summaries that clearly communicate findings to internal stakeholders and executives.
Explain complex modeling approaches in simple terms and develop compelling narratives that connect data analysis with business problems.
Use best-in-class methods to establish causal relationships between product decisions and customer behavior and sentiment.
Contribute to building the data-driven culture in Salesforce.


Job Requirements
Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in statistics, computer science, economics, or a related quantitative field,
MBA or Management consulting experience is a plus.
5+ years of experience in data analysis.
Advanced expert in SQL. Experience with Splunk, Python/R, and BI tools.
Direct experience working with large data-sets, joining data from multiple sources and different levels of analysis.
Lover of math with solid understanding of statistical methods. Practical experience with statistical and machine learning models: ANOVA, multiple regression, decision trees, clustering analysis.
Experience leading data-driven projects from definition to execution, driving impact and influencing product and business roadmaps.
Communication and presentation experience with a proven track record of using insights to influence executives and colleagues, and presenting research data in a compelling manner that inspires action.
Expert in building relationships and collaborating in a matrixed environment, working effectively with a variety of individuals and organizations.
Curious, creative, opinionated thinker with a talent for detecting patterns and elevating through strategy.
Laser focused on impact, balancing effort to value, and getting things done.
Self-starter who is able to work effectively without excessive supervision.
Enterprise software geek. Passion for Salesforce products is a plus!

title: Business Operations Manager
description:
Who Is Bird
At Bird, we’re on a mission to make cities more livable by reducing traffic and carbon emissions with an affordable, convenient, and eco-friendly transportation option. We planted roots in Los Angeles, California. Now, our fleet of electric scooters is available to riders in cities around the world for short trips or the “last mile” of their journey. In our first year, Bird launched in over 100 cities and provided over 10 million rides. And we’re only just getting started.
The Business Operations Manager will champion high priority projects for our VP of Global Strategy. In this role, you will amplify the profitable growth of our business through tackling key business priorities, scaling best practices, and implementing operational improvements. We need a strategic critical thinker who can draw upon strong operational and analytical experience to start at 30,000 feet and then dive deep into the details to ensure high quality results.
The ideal candidate for this role should have a “doer” attitude, strong strategic skills, excellent time-management and organizational habits, and the ability to clearly communicate and present information to seek buy-in.
Responsibilities:
Develop frameworks and drive data analysis on strategic priorities in order to optimize our business and solve the biggest problems as they arise
Partner cross-functionally with other members of the Bird team to measure the impact and efficiency of processes, while identifying new ways to create value for the business Incubate and test new solutions to business problems, and scale the highest potential solutions from ideation through global implementation
Oversee business performance reporting and own strategic content distribution to executive leadership
Be a hard-working multitasker, supporting teams in multiple locations. You’ll be one of the go to people when the business requires solutions to fire drills
Requirements:
Bachelor's degree or equivalent
4-7+ years of relevant experience in business strategy / consulting, investment banking, business intelligence or related; experience at a high growth startup is a plus
Qualifications:
Exceptional communication and organization skills
Balance attention to detail with swift execution – we need to do things quickly, and we need to do them well
Explorer – the ability to self-serve, investigate and get the data we require will make you much more effective in this role
A “get it done” attitude – bias toward action, great collaboration and master disambiguation – constantly pushing toward clarity and delivery
Strong Excel, Powerpoint, and data analysis capabilities
Culture at Bird
We're an ambitious, smart, and open-minded group. Our employees are passionate about our mission, and eager to complete their work at the highest level. The office itself is up tempo and supportive, because we care about each other. People first, people.
Perks up
We want people to succeed at Bird, so we give our teams plenty of time off to relax and recharge. We also offer generous employer-paid healthcare coverage, on-demand doctor visits, childcare support, a pre-tax commuter account for mass transit or parking, a wellness stipend, and more.
Bird is the world
Bird stands for a culture of inclusion. We celebrate different backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives —encouraging everyone to bring their authentic selves to work. We have a diverse environment that empowers our team to feel comfortable when they voice their opinions. For these reasons and more Bird is a proud equal employment opportunity employer. We welcome everyone regardless of their race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, or genetics, and we are dedicated to providing an inclusive, open, and diverse work environment.
Sound like a place you’d like to work? Sweet. Let’s chat.

title: Head of Advanced Analytics: Global CS
location: San Jose, CA 95131 (North San Jose area)
description:
Who we are: Fueled by a fundamental belief that having access to financial services creates opportunity, PayPal (NASDAQ: PYPL) is committed to democratizing financial services and empowering people and businesses to join and thrive in the global economy. Our open digital payments platform gives PayPal’s 286 million active account holders the confidence to connect and transact in new and powerful ways, whether they are online, on a mobile device, in an app, or in person. Through a combination of technological innovation and strategic partnerships, PayPal creates better ways to manage and move money, and offers choice and flexibility when sending payments, paying or getting paid. Available in more than 200 markets around the world, the PayPal platform, including Braintree, Venmo and Xoom enables consumers and merchants to receive money in more than 100 currencies, withdraw funds in 56 currencies and hold balances in their PayPal accounts in 25 currencies.
Job Description Summary: Our global sales transformation is in full swing. We embarked on a path of transforming and building a world class sales organization earlier this year. Our team helps to power PayPal’s high growth Sales organization by delivering actionable insights and business intelligence at scale to all levels of the business - our customers, our front-line Sales teams and our executive leadership team. You will partner with these teams to understand the insights they require to manage and grow their business and leverage cross-functional teams to develop and land solutions that meet their needs at scale. You are deeply curious and persistent in gaining knowledge about our products and go-to-market strategy. Experience with Salesforce.com

title: Senior AX Business Analyst
description:
HM Electronics has been creating innovative products for the drive-thru and pro-audio industries since 1971. From the very beginning, we have known these solutions would never have happened without the customer-focused people who make up our company. HME has a team environment with a culture of collaboration, learning, and growth. With subsidiaries located in California, Georgia, Missouri, Canada, UK, and China, companies around the world depend on HME for clear, reliable communication solutions. From setting the standard for drive-thru headsets and timer systems in the quick service restaurant (QSR) industry to developing professional audio equipment used in the Olympic Games, HME strives to create the newest, most innovative products on the market while providing quality care and attention to its customers. Come join our team!
We are currently recruiting for a Senior AX Business Analyst. In this role, you will be responsible for supporting and enhancing HME’s ERP system, Dynamics AX. You will be working with departments across the organization researching and analyzing requirements to help solve complex business problems. In addition, you will develop and implement solutions to meet the needs of the business. As the Sr. Business Analyst, you will coordinate with end users to improve system functionality and provide guidance on best practices and use of the system. Lastly, you will also work closely with AX developers to design test protocols and establish testing metrics.
What you will do in the position:
Coordinate with Dynamics AX end users to improving system functionality and ensuring that end users can perform their day to day duties in Dynamics AX.
Research requirements and document solutions for functions and processes to further improve and enhance business utilization of Dynamics AX.
Work with AX end-users and AX team to develop and implement enhancements and changes, facilitate communication and understanding of requirements and processes between the AX team and end-users.
Assist in configuration changes and customizations in Dynamics AX.
Assist in testing and validating system changes, upgrades, and enhancements.
Assist in managing the requirements process post-implementation.
Provide technical leadership in projects related to Dynamics AX.
What you will need to succeed in this position:
Strong knowledge of ERP systems.
Expert knowledge of Trade and Logistics functionality including Advanced Warehouse, Shipping, Sales and Service modules.
Minimum 5 years’ experience with Dynamics AX 2012 in a Business Analyst role with at least 1 full lifecycle implementation.
Third-party application integration experience a plus.
Experience with ISV's and PowerBI a plus.
Knowledge and experience writing functional requirements and leveraging AX for business intelligence.
Able to complete tasks in a timely manner and act independently on routine assignments or projects.
Able to make oral presentations clear, concise and easy to understand.
Possess skills in problem-solving; including the ability to identify and appropriately evaluate a course of action.
Able to pay attention to details and perform at a high level of accuracy.

Experience
5+ years Related Field
Education
BA or BS (college graduate) - preferred Information Systems
Travel
10%

About HME
We are committed to building a company where highly talented, challenge-hungry people thrive. You will have the opportunity to learn and grow while making a real contribution to our product. Our benefits package includes tuition reimbursement; 3 weeks of paid vacation you the first year, paid holidays, medical, vision, and dental coverage, life insurance, and 401K contributions.

Physical Demands & Work Environment
The physical demands and work the environment described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.
While performing the duties of this job, the employee is frequently required to use hands to handle or manipulate objects. The employee is regularly required to talk or hear, stand, walk, sit, work with computer and office equipment, machinery, or electrical tools, and reach with hands and arms. The employee is occasionally required to climb or balance, and stoop, kneel, crouch, or crawl.

The position requires frequent contact outside the department or company and the noise level in the work environment is usually quiet to moderate with an occasional loud noise. The employee occasionally works near moving mechanical parts works in high, precarious places is exposed to fumes and/or airborne particles, toxic or caustic chemicals, outdoor weather conditions, and is regularly at risk of electric shock.

About HME
Five companies. One family name. The HME family of companies is the leading provider of clear, reliable communication solutions for a variety of niche markets; from world-famous restaurant chains to major television networks and global live events to military, aerospace, and government applications - HME products are preferred in 100+ countries.

title: Senior Business Intelligence Analyst
description:
Unity Technologies is looking for an analytical, detail oriented, and motivated individual to join our Business Operations team as a Senior Business Operations Analyst. Analytical: You are comfortable taking a quantitative approach to problem solving and comfortable with financial modeling

The company's 1,400+ person research and development team keeps Unity at the forefront of development by working alongside partners to ensure optimized support for the latest releases and platforms. title: Lead Business Intelligence Architect
location: San Diego, CA 92108 (Mission Valley East area)
description:
Who We Are

At Hyundai Translead, we promote a customer-driven corporate culture by providing the best quality and impeccable service with all values centered on our customers. We refuse to be complacent, embracing every opportunity for greater challenge and are confident in achieving our goals with unwavering passion and ingenious thinking. We create synergy through a sense of “togetherness” that is fostered by mutual communication and cooperation within the company and with our business partners. We believe the future of our organization lies in the hearts and capabilities of individual members, and will help them develop their potential by creating a corporate culture that respects talent. We respect the diversity of culture and customers, aspire to be the world’s best at what we do, and strive to become a respected global corporate citizen.
Job Summary
Hyundai Translead seeks a candidate to lead the sales organization's efforts around customer experience to include commercial insight identification, CRM administration, and sales tool generation. The Lead Business Intelligence Architect will have a hands-on lead role in designing, creating, and maintaining commercially facing systems for the business. This role will encompass all products and will interface with a variety of business functions including engineering, finance, operations, IT, general management, and sales. To be successful, this role must gain a full understanding of the sales and business processes to ensure system implementations flow with the natural progression of the sale. This role will also be required to interact with customers of the business in an effort to gain understanding and voice of the customer first hand. Ultimately, these interactions will translate into broader business strategy through commercial system implementations. Initial responsibility includes implementing a CRM system based upon stakeholder feedback as well as creating various sales tools to leverage CRM and SAP data. Ultimately, the role will transition into a broader role incorporating more Customer Experience based tools and systems in line with the broader commercial strategy of the business.
This role will grow and evolve with the organization and is key to commercial system consistency in approach, architecture and design leading to the enablement of talent portability. Training on specific systems to be utilized will be provided. Hard coding of interfaces/API’s is not required.

title: Director, Data Analytics
location: San Jose, CA 95112 (North San Jose area)
description:
Company Overview
Outset is a medical technology company pioneering a first-of-its-kind technology to reduce the cost and complexity of dialysis. The Tablo Hemodialysis System, FDA cleared for use from the hospital to the home, represents a significant technological advancement that transforms the dialysis experience for patients and operationally simplifies it for providers. Tablo serves as a single enterprise solution that can be utilized across the continuum of care, allowing dialysis to be delivered anytime, anywhere and by anyone. The integration of water purification and on-demand dialysate production enables Tablo to serve as a dialysis clinic on wheels, with 2-way wireless data transmission and a proprietary data analytics platform powering a new holistic approach to dialysis care.

Position Overview
Outset is looking for a hands-on Director to lead the development of data analytics services across the company. The Director will manage software developers, business analysts, and a tester to develop data analytics services. This person will be responsible for the business analytics, data analytics, data science and the machine learning platform. The Director will collaborate with business leaders, data science teams, product management, program management, and other members across the organization and leadership team of the company to build effective data analytics for Outset.

In this role, you should be passionate about working with massive datasets and be someone who loves to bring useful quality data together to answer business questions. You should have deep expertise in the creation and management of datasets and the proven ability to select the right technologies for the platform to create meaningful insights. The ideal candidate will bring deep expertise in machine learning and data management while enabling organization growth with effective and accurate data. You will need to have in-depth experience with data visualization and expert in presenting insights to engineers to executives in the company.

Ideal candidates must have excellent problem-solving skills, a high degree of attention to detail, strong organizational skills, and a proven track record developing enterprise-grade data analytics. This leadership position is an excellent opportunity to work for a growing medical device startup.

Responsibilities/Functions
Engage with business and customers to understand customer requirements, timeline, resource availability
Technical expert for big data analytics, machine learning
Lead, manage, and execute a company-wide data analytic vision to consistently leverage data, tools, and data quality best practices for optimal business processing, adoption of data, and critical decision making within the Outset.
Team building, stakeholder management, and player/coach skills are essential to delivering business results.
Anticipate new trends and customer needs and find new and innovative ways to solve complex challenges as the team implements its internal and external data initiatives.
Implement end-to-end data solutions, support, and the senior leadership teams in their day to day testing and business needs.
Lead cross-functional teams on projects and partner with business owners in identifying data sources and quality issues and develop a data quality framework
Develop a data platform to support broader business initiatives
Collaborate closely with the analysts and scientists across the organization
Maintain a strong personal base of knowledge of data platform technology, medical industry practices, trends and issues
Play a major role in the direction and strategy of the Outset data engineering roadmap adding critical value to the organization
Lead and mentor team of software developers
Ensure proper policies and procedures are in place
Provide technical direction to the team
Influence technology decisions as a member of our engineering leadership team
Participate in Scrum ceremonies and keep task notes and daily update progress in our ticketing system.
Requirements/Qualifications
BS Degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, or related field
Minimum of 12+ years of data analytics platform development
Experience with machine learning and big data technologies
Experience with business intelligence and visualization technology, including Tableau and D3.js
Experience leading diverse cross-functional teams, mentoring and managing stakeholders across business units and technology
Experience leading company-wide data programs, business acumen, and technical expertise in data space, self-service analytics, and data governance processes
Passionate about data quality and love working with business intelligence tools, can partner with business owners to answer critical questions
Analytical, innovative, creative, and disruptive.
Ability to establish and maintain cooperative and productive working relationships with people at all levels of Outset; build morale and team spirit among team members
Communicate clearly and effectively both orally and in writing with persons having diverse backgrounds of knowledge and experience; conduct meetings and make professional presentations; teach complex concepts and explain technical material to non-technical users
Conceive and initiate projects; improvise and invent solutions in new, non-standard and unstructured situations
Works well through ambiguity; confidence in making tough calls and leading through adversity with a sharp focus on the eventual right outcomes
Medical device experience is a plus
Must have a proven portfolio of successful projects in areas mentioned above

title: Data Engineering Manager, Analytics - Facebook Reality Labs
description:
Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities - we're just getting started.
Come invent the future. At Facebook Reality Labs, software development is vital to turbocharging our scientific explorations and generating viable paths to the consumer products people will use for decades to come, products that will literally give people super powers. As a Data Engineering Manager, you’ll work closely with product teams and other cross functional partners as part of the Facebook Reality Labs Privacy team by establishing privacy controls to ensure we can collect and process data to help inform product direction and confirm hypotheses. We primarily work closely with Product Managers, Software Engineers, Data Scientists and User Researchers to build and leverage a scalable data architecture foundation. You’ll be able to see your efforts affect products and people on a regular basis. The ideal candidate will have data infrastructure and data architecture skills as well as experience driving large data privacy initiatives, a proven track record of leading and scaling data teams, strong operational skills to drive efficiency and speed, strong project management leadership, and a strong vision for how data can proactively improve companies.
Proactively drive the vision for BI and Data Privacy across Facebook Reality Labs, and define and execute on a plan to achieve that vision.
Define the processes needed to achieve operational excellence in all areas, including project management and system reliability.
Build a high-quality BI and Data Warehousing privacy focused team and design the team to scale.
Build cross-functional relationships with Data Scientists, Product Managers and Software Engineers to understand data needs and deliver on those needs.
Manage privacy data warehouse plans across Facebook Reality Labs.
Drive the design, building, and launching of new data models and data pipelines in production.
Drive data quality across the product vertical and related business areas.
Manage the delivery of high impact dashboards and data visualizations.
Define and manage SLA’s for all data sets and processes running in production.

8+ years of experience in Business Intelligence and Data Warehousing.
Experience scaling and managing 3+ person teams.
Communication and leadership experience, with experience initiating and driving projects.
Project management experience.
Data architecture experience.
Experience in SQL or similar languages.
Development experience in at least one object-oriented language (Python, Java, etc.).
BA/BS in Computer Science, Math, Physics, or other technical fields.

title: Senior Business Intelligence Engineer
description:
Join SADA as a Sr. BI Engineer!
Your Mission
As a Sr. Business Insights/Intelligence Engineer at SADA, you will work collaboratively with key business leads, architects, analysts and data scientists to understand the business domain and how data can empower them. You engage with fellow engineers to develop better data platforms to make the process of producing data and deriving insights is easy and efficient. You will have an opportunity to work on proposing and defining metrics for business reporting and product/process performance monitoring for our customers. Engagements vary from being purely consultative to requiring heavy hands-on work, and cover a diverse array of domain areas, such as BI tool migrations and big data analytics solutions.
You will be expected to run point on whole projects, end-to-end, and to mentor less experienced BI Engineers/Data Analysts. You will be recognized as an expert within the team and will build a reputation with Google and our customers. The successful candidate will demonstrate business acumen, experience in developing reporting and analytical infrastructures and ability to work effectively with cross functional teams in a fast paced environment. You should have excellent business and communication skills to collaborate with business owners to draw insights from data to answer questions to key business questions. You will also participate in early-stage opportunity qualification calls, as well as lead client-facing technical discussions for established projects.
Pathway to Success
#BeOneStepAhead: At SADA Systems we are in the business of change. We are focused on leading-edge technology that is ever-evolving. We embrace change enthusiastically and encourage agility. This means that not only do our engineers know that change is inevitable, but they embrace this change to continuously expand their skills, preparing for future customer needs.
Your success starts by positively impacting the direction of a fast growing practice with vision and passion. You will be measured quarterly by the breadth, magnitude and quality of your contributions, your ability to estimate accurately, customer feedback at the close of projects, how well you collaborate with your peers, and the consultative polish you bring to customer interactions.
As you continue to execute successfully, we will build a customized development plan together that leads you through the engineering or management growth tracks.
Expectations
Required Travel - 30% travel to customer sites, conferences, and other related events. Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, travel has been temporarily restricted.
Customer Facing - You will interact with customers on a regular basis, sometimes daily, other times weekly/bi-weekly. Common touchpoints occur when qualifying potential opportunities, at project kickoff, throughout the engagement as progress is communicated, and at project close. You can expect to interact with a range of customer stakeholders, including engineers, technical project managers, and executives.
Training - Ongoing with first week orientation at HQ followed by a 90 day onboarding schedule. Details of timeline can be shared.
Job Requirements
Required Credentials:
LookML Developer Certification or able to complete within the first 45 days of employment
Expert or Professional level certifications in other BI tools like Cognos, OBIEE, BOBJ, Microstrategy, Qlik, and Thoughtspot
Required Qualifications:
Experience in business intelligence role, including data warehousing, business intelligence, data visualization tools, techniques and technology
Experience with upgrade and migration of legacy BI Tools to data visualization tools like Tableau, Looker etc.
Experience in designing and delivering cross functional custom reporting solutions.
Experience with an enterprise class BI tool like Micro Strategy, Business Objects, Tableau, Oracle Business Intelligence, Cognos, PowerBI and familiarity with new BI tools like Domo, Looker or Superset
Experience gathering business requirements, using business intelligence tools to extract data, formulate metrics, & build reports
Experience with query development and tuning.
Experience working in very large data warehouse environments
Experience conducting large scale data analysis to support business decision making
Excellent oral and written communication skills including the ability to communicate effectively with both technical and non-technical stakeholders.
Proven ability to meet tight deadlines, multi-task, and prioritize workload
Track record for being detail-oriented with a demonstrated ability to self-motivate and follow-through on projects
Useful Qualifications:
Bachelor's degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Engineering, or a related technical field
Experience working with Google Cloud data products (CloudSQL, Spanner, Cloud Storage, Bigtable, BigQuery, Dataprep, etc)
Experience with programming languages such as Python, Scala, Java, R
Demonstrated leadership and self-direction - willingness to teach others and learn new techniques
Time series analysis, clustering, decision trees and neural networks
About SADA
Values: We built our core values on themes that internally compel us to deliver our best to our partners, our customers and to each other. Ensuring a diverse and inclusive workplace where we learn from each other is core to SADA's values. We welcome people of different backgrounds, experiences, abilities and perspectives. We are an equal opportunity employer.
Make them rave
Be data driven
Be one step ahead
Be a change agent
Do the right thing
Work with the best: SADA has been the largest partner in North America for GCP since 2016 and recently announced, at Google NEXT, as the 2018 Global Partner of the Year. SADA has also been awarded Best Place to Work by Inc. as well as LA Business Journal!
Benefits: Unlimited PTO, competitive and attractive compensation, performance-based bonuses, paid holidays, rich medical, dental, vision plans, life, short and long-term disability insurance, 401K with match, professional development reimbursement program as well as Google Certified training programs.
Business Performance: SADA has been named to the INC 5000 Fastest Growing Private Companies list for 12 years in a row garnering Honoree status. CRN has also named SADA on the Top 500 Global Solutions Providers for the past 5 years. The overall culture continues to evolve with engineering at its core: 3200+ projects completed, 3000+ customers served, 10K+ workloads and 25M+ users migrated to the cloud.

title: Director, GTM Advanced Analytics
description:
Because you belong at Twilio
The Who, What, Why and Where
Twilio is growing rapidly and seeking a Director, GTM Advanced Analytics with a demonstrated track record of excellence in developing and managing advanced analytics capabilities. As a leader in our Sales Strategy & Analytics team you will expand the use of our business intelligence platforms and the underlying data infrastructure supporting them, unite our analytics efforts across Sales, Marketing, Customer Success, Product, and Finance, develop sophisticated new advanced analytics capabilities, and lead change management that "future-proofs" our business.
The Director of GTM Advanced Analytics will act as a management consultant and operational leader helping Twilio to clarify fast-moving strategic priorities and tackle operational challenges.
Who?
Twilio is looking for a leader who lives the Twilio Magic and has a demonstrated track record of leading Go-To-Market analytics. They also have:
Expert level command of the tools of our trade: Tableau, SQL, Salesforce, Python or other coding languages.
Experience implementing machine learning and statistical models into real world applications.
Thrives at structured strategic thinking, analytical processing, problem-solving, synthesizing ideas, and written and verbal communication.
Can ruthlessly prioritize fast-moving strategic priorities, tackle operational challenges, and drive change through hyper-growth.
Will become a trusted business partner to GTM leadership, and play a critical role scaling the company's rapidly growing GTM organization.
Has 8+ years relevant experience in business intelligence and/or the software industry.
Bachelor's degree or equivalent experience required.
What?
As the Director of GTM Advanced Analytics, you will live the Twilio Magic values:
BE BOLD & BE AN OWNER: Become intimately familiar with the business, lead the team to distill and deliver critical business insights for leadership, and influence teammates and executives with your findings;
DRAW THE OWL: Expand Twilio Go-To-Market's Tableau instance, including the evolution of new dashboards to meet business partner needs;
EMPOWER OTHERS: Lead, mentor, and optimize productivity across our business analytics teams.
BE INCLUSIVE & RUTHLESSLY PRIORITIZE: You will collaborate closely with business owners across functions, fully immerse yourself and your team in data, draw insight from analysis, and then zoom out to develop compelling, synthesized recommendations. Analytical rigor and strategic thinking are a must, but you'll also need to get your hands dirty to drive real, sustainable impact
Why?
The Sales Strategy & Analytics team is central to Twilio's continued growth. We work closely with senior leadership and product teams to guide company strategy. We lead all aspects of identifying, evaluating, and executing strategies that drive inorganic growth and have a significant impact on the overall direction of the company. Increasingly, we require advanced predictive and prescriptive capabilities to optimize the business.
Twilio is a company that is empowering the world's developers with modern communication in order to build better applications. Twilio is truly unique; we are a company committed to your growth, your learning, your development, and your entire employee experience. We only win when our employees succeed and we're dedicated to helping you develop your strengths. We have a cultural foundation built on diversity, inclusion, and innovation and we want you and your ideas to thrive at Twilio.
Where?
We employ diverse talent from all over the world and we believe great work can be done anywhere. Around the world, Twilio offers benefits and perks to support the physical, financial, and emotional well being of you and your loved ones. No matter where you are based, you will experience a company that believes in small teams for maximum impact; seeks well-rounded talent to ensure a full perspective on our customers' experience, understands that this is a marathon, not a sprint; that continuously and purposefully builds an inclusive culture that empowers everyone to do their best work and be the best version of themselves.
About us:
Millions of developers around the world have used Twilio to unlock the magic of communications to improve any human experience. Twilio has democratized communications channels like voice, text, chat, video and email by virtualizing the world's communications infrastructure through APIs that are simple enough for any developer to use, yet robust enough to power the world's most demanding applications. By making communications a part of every software developer's toolkit, Twilio is enabling innovators across every industry — from emerging leaders to the world's largest organizations — to reinvent how companies engage with their customers.

title: Senior Developer / Business Intelligence Report Analyst
description:
Masimo (NASDAQ: MASI) headquartered in Irvine, California, is a fast-growing and award-winning international medical technology and device company with operations spanning the globe. We develop innovative, noninvasive monitoring technologies that save, extend and improve the lives of people of all ages, in all walks of life. These revolutionary technologies are helping to solve "unsolvable" problems that have plagued the healthcare industry, while taking the pain and discomfort out of blood monitoring. For more than 25 years, innovation has been and will continue to be our passion.
To learn more about us, please visit: www.masimo.com
Job Summary
The Senior Business Intelligence Report Analyst will be responsible for continual interface and support of Masimo’s internal & global business community, with our technical development team. The Analyst should possess hands-on expertise in Microsoft Power BI, SQL Server Database Design and Architecture, Business Intelligence Application Design, Oracle EBS, SDLC, and other key Microsoft Development Technologies. This position will manage daily BI Enterprise Application support, request for new reporting requirements and deliver training to our BI user community, and may either work independently or actively collaborate as a team lead or member.
Duties & Responsibilities

Actively executes to key reporting functions, including:
Development of SQL Server ETL, SSIS, SSAS and SSRS
Development of management Dashboards, Scorecards and KPI’s, per business requirements
Customization of BI Reporting, where necessary, utilizing Microsoft PowerBI, Crystal Reports, Excel
Design of BI reports & documents, per business requirements
Deliver BI-related user trainings
Support of Business Intelligence Application and platform
Collaborates with stakeholders, development teams and other groups in system development and support activities
Creates and maintains Power BI Dashboards, Reports and KPIs
Continually develops, migrates, and enhances/upgrades reports, applications and databases
Codes, debugs and tests (utilizing concepts of use cases, test scripts, unit/integration/acceptance)
Works with traditional software lifecycle methodologies
Reviews and discerns business requirements, writes design specifications, and provides recommendations to proposed solution
Develops functional requirements, process/data workflows, and system design specifications
Develops, coordinates, and delivers BI training for internal users and management
Collaborates with other teams (projects, BSAs, integration, etc.) in the implementation of proposed IT/IS solutions
Interacts and supports executive-level reporting, as needed

Minimum Qualifications

Five plus (5+) years of Microsoft Power BI and SQL Server
Five plus (5+) years of systems analysis, design, development, and support experience
Familiarity with Microsoft applications stack, including MS Office 365 and Azure
Hands-on knowledge of design and maintenance of SAP WebI dashboards and reports
Knowledge of current development tools, technologies, languages, frameworks and trends is beneficial
Excellent object-oriented design & programming skills
Technical skills and experience with:
BI tools - MS PowerBI, SAP Webi (others – Tableau a plus)
Data marts, data warehouse concepts
Microsoft’s SSAS, SSIS, SSRS and other corporate reporting tools
Demonstrated ability to write and execute intermediate to advanced SQL (data retrieval and analysis
Demonstrated knowledge of data processing and databases
Knowledge of Oracle EBS (E-Business Suite) and Oracle PL SQL
Excellent aptitude in problem solving, analysis, critical thinking, troubleshooting, & recommendations in proposed solutions
Experience working closely with technical developers, in articulating or collaborating on technical specifications & requirements
Ability to effectively communicate, organize and get work done with minimal supervision
Ability to multi-task, interact well with business, and work well under time pressure
Ability to organize and conduct user trainings

Preferred Qualifications

Technical expertise in development and support of SQL Server environment and Microsoft Development Platform
Technical experience in application integration to ERP and company standard applications
Experience in supporting Business Analytics or Business Intelligence Application
Experience in BI dashboards and reports migration
Technical skills may include:
Demonstrated knowledge & experience of ERP and manufacturing systems
Demonstrated knowledge & experience supporting other mission critical IS applications, including Salesforce and EDI

Education
Bachelor degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or related field is required. Power BI certification - a plus
Physical requirements/Work Environment
This position primarily works in an office environment. It requires frequent sitting, standing and walking. Daily use of a computer and other computing and digital devices is required. May stand for extended periods when facilitating meetings or walking in the facilities. Frequent lifting of equipment up to 60lbs. Some local travel is necessary, so the ability to operate a motor vehicle and maintain a valid Driver’s license is required.
The physical demands of the position described herein are essential functions of the job and employees must be able to successfully perform these tasks for extended periods. Reasonable accommodations may be made for those individuals with real or perceived disabilities to perform the essential functions of the job described.
Masimo is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex including sexual orientation and gender identity, national origin, disability, protected Veteran Status, or any other characteristic protected by applicable federal, state or local law.
***NO AGENCIES PLEASE*** Thank you!

title: Enterprise Analytics Lead
description:
Mission - Partners with UCSF Health leaders, as a trusted advisor, to enable data insights and facilitate The delivery of innovative solutions which create systemic value
Vision - Accelerate UCSF Health strategy using data to understand the past, manage the present and transform the future
Values - Compassion, Teamwork, Diversity, Accountability, Innovation
Provides client facing, consultative services to operations by gathering business & functional requirements, and set the stage for client engagement and user standards. Facilitates the successful hand-off to technical, reporting, and infrastructure teams. Acts as a solutions consultant for the business’ analytical needs
Manages the project’s framework, processes and methodologies involving departmental or cross-functional teams. Plans, coordinates and monitors scope, requirements, schedules, budgets, resources, tasks, risks, staff and deliverables. Monitors the project from initiation through completion. Organizes and leads activities relating to the management and completion of projects. May provide customer service, troubleshooting and maintenance
Accountable for providing leadership and independent initiatives in facilitating and conducting information gathering, structured documentation and presentation of findings
Involves the development of forecasts, recommendations, and strategic / tactical plans based on business data and market knowledge
Researches new technology and develops business cases to support enterprise-wide business intelligence solutions.
Optimizes the performance of enterprise business intelligence tools by defining data to filter and index that add value to the user.
The Enterprise Analytics Solutions Consultant Lead is responsible for providing healthcare enterprise analytics, subject matter expertise and consulting practice leadership with a goal to drive business growth and discovery. Applies advanced technical project management frameworks and methods and UCSF Health objectives with a strong emphasis on enterprise analytics and business development, will help to achieve its growth, meet project objectives and maintain a best practice. Experienced professional who knows how to apply theory and put it into practice with in-depth understanding of the professional field and the health care system environment. Coordination at the Enterprise level the strategic partnerships and collaborations of franchise and / or departmental data assets to determine and / or create assets of higher value for enterprise use. Candidate will have the ability to influence people that do not directly report to them and hence must possess strong inter-personal skills such as team building, consensus building, diplomacy, persuasiveness and the ability to create a positive a work environment. As a senior member of the EA team, the EA Project Management / Analyst Lead will join professionals with a broad knowledge of the healthcare industry including: Financial analysis and revenue performance management, regulatory reporting, compliance, healthcare IT, education and research. The EA Project Manager / Analytics Lead will be an integral part of a collaborative consulting team to deliver exceptional client service to meet UCSF data and analytics objectives.

Under direction of the UCSF Associate Director of Enterprise Analytics, the EA Project Manager / Analytics Lead will be the key individual responsible for coordination of planning, designing, architecting, and managing implementation and support of Enterprise Analytics solutions. The individual will leverage healthcare expertise related to the product in assessment of any risks the application release may contain, as well as to assess impacts to all products resulted from upgrades or maintenance. This individual will work closely with all members of the organization both inpatient and outpatient, including campus and health system areas at UCSF. The EA Project Manager / Analytics Lead will provide support where needed to Associate Director of Enterprise Analytics and stand in as department Associate Director when requested. The right candidate will understand well, the partnership, collaboration and teamwork needed with key business and technology leaders to achieve success in this endeavor.
Department Description
The Enterprise Analytics department functions as the liaison between the customer or partners in the organization and technical resources to provide optimal analytic solutions to solve problems, answer questions and meet the needs of our customers. Key partners include clinical, financial, administration, and campus domains. The team is involved in strategic and operational activities to both inform and drive change in behaviors and ultimately outcomes through use of data and information.

The University of California San Francisco (UCSF) Department of Information Technology is seeking a qualified individual to lead the design, analysis, presentation and dissemination of data, information and knowledge critical to the performance of UCSF enterprise wide.
Required Qualifications
Five-plus years of project leadership / management experience or in consulting with senior managers on Enterprise Analytics (EA) operations / quantitative management OR demonstrated implementation of EA dashboards at UCSF
Three to five years’ experience in health care business intelligence / analytics reporting, data mining, data analysis, and/or statistical analysis OR minimum two years of experience in healthcare business data management/ analysis and support, EA or IT consulting
Minimum three (3) years of experience in information systems development, implementation of software development life cycle, with progressively more complex responsibilities and accountabilities in a large mainframe or client server environment
Bachelor's degree required in Health Care Administration, Business Administration or related field or equivalent education/experince
In-depth understanding of general business functions, processes, and overall business strategies preferably in the healthcare industry for areas including Inpatient / Outpatient environments, ACOs, network management, physician profiling, population health management, and care management
Advanced analytical skills and expertise in documentation and reporting
Strong project management / consulting skills with focus on managing multiple projects and consistently delivering on time and within budget that meet or exceed stakeholders' expectations. Effective skill at tracking effort and project progress. Demonstrated highly advanced organization and project management skills. Demonstrated strong conceptual and planning skills to analyze projects of broad and diverse scope. Understands the cost impact of projects, project tracking tools and metrics
Successful track record of eliciting, defining, creating, and analyzing functional and non-functional requirements, developing system design and architecture, system configuration, testing and deployment. With proven aptitude in the delivery of high-quality products in short timelines
Strong critical thinking and problem-solving skills to lead teams, manage complex information, assess problems, and develop effective solutions. Ability to demonstrate excellent judgment, attention to process and detail.
Strong analytical skills and knowledge in documentation and reporting, with the ability to collect and analyze system performance data, and produce substantive reports and analyses
Thorough knowledge of business intelligence functions, analytics, industry standards and best practices
Demonstrated ability to integrate critical information across disciplines. Understands how projects relate to other business strategies and initiatives
Demonstrated ability to clearly articulate User Stories and Conditions of Satisfaction to development teams including Physician, Nursing, Pharmacy, Lab, and Respiratory
Ability to work with senior staff and managers in clinical information technology, health care management, and business analytics, serving as a technical resource and providing advice and counsel on issues of functionality, efficiency, cost-effectiveness, policy, and performance
Discretion, confidentiality, tact, and ability to deal with sensitive data involving patient health information
Customer Service
Prioritization
Communication
Technical Skills:
Three plus years’ experience with data analysis software such as MS Office Suite (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Access)
Highly experienced in database applications, and analytical software (such as Qlikview, Tableau, R, or others, certification a plus)
Leadership:
Dependable, self-motivated and able to work with minimal supervision
Have a strong sense of leadership & entrepreneurial spirit
Be a self-starter & highly respected people leader
Be result oriented
High level of accuracy and attention to detail
Flexibility to orient and work at all UCSF locations
Preferred Qualifications
Thorough knowledge of relevant internal databases, BI applications and tools, such as APeX / Epic (Clarity, Caboodle, etc) and proficient in SQL programming
Prior experience in the use of business intelligence tools such as SAP Universe, Web Intelligence and Crystal Reports and performing complex data analysis with large volumes of data.
Prior experience developing self-service analytic tools utilizing Tableau desktop and / or Tableau server
Familiarity with health care environment Licensure/Certification
Experience working with agile development process
Knowledge of statistical process control principles
Consulting experience a plus - a professional service industry environment within a global matrix
Demonstration of healthcare enterprise analytics thought leadership a plus (white papers/articles, speaking experience, etc)
Six Sigma Black Belt certification highly desirable.
Master’s Degree in Health Sciences or Business related field, statistics, epidemiology, public health, operations research, computers / systems engineering or other relevant field OR 8+ years in healthcare data analysis and support or equivalent work experience
Registered Nurse or other currently licensed healthcare professional
Six Sigma Black Belt certification
Project Management certification
EPIC Certification in one or more Cogito, Clinical (Ambulatory or Inpatient) or Revenue Cycle application(s)
About UCSF
At UCSF Health, our mission of innovative patient care, advanced technology and pioneering research is redefining what’s possible for the patients we serve – a promise we share with the professionals who make up our team.

Consistently ranked among the top 10 hospitals nationwide by U.S. News & World Report – UCSF Health is committed to providing the most rewarding work experience while delivering the best care available anywhere. In an environment that allows for continuous learning and opportunities for professional growth, UCSF Health offers the ideal atmosphere in which to best use your skills and talents. as seventh in the country – UCSF Health is committed to providing the most rewarding work experience while delivering the best care available anywhere. Pride Values
UCSF is a diverse community made of people with many skills and talents. We seek candidates whose work experience or community service has prepared them to contribute to our commitment to professionalism, respect, integrity, diversity and excellence – also known as our PRIDE values.

In addition to our PRIDE values, UCSF is committed to equity – both in how we deliver care as well as our workforce. We are committed to building a broadly diverse community, nurturing a culture that is welcoming and supportive, and engaging diverse ideas for the provision of culturally competent education, discovery, and patient care. title: Director, Analytics
description:
Hims and Hers offers a modern approach to health and wellness. Our mission is to eliminate stigmas and make it easier for people to access care and treatment for the conditions that impact their daily lives. That starts with creating an open and honest culture of care that is accessible for everyone, no matter who you are or where you live. Since launching in November 2017, we've raised over $200MM in funding and are one of the fastest growing direct-to-consumer brands in history.
Hims and Hers is looking for an experienced, hands-on growth minded analytics leader who can help drive forward our Marketing, Product Experience, and Wholesale efforts. You'll help lead projects focusing on key company initiatives to efficiently deploy marketing dollars and optimize the conversion funnel for various treatments offered on our platform.
Responsibilities:
Help drive Marketing & Product initiatives that employ new strategies and technology solutions in an effort to increase customer acquisition, patient engagement, and product sales
Project manage the development of data models and algorithms to help us understand our marketing tactics better, especially as it relates to acquisition channel attribution, customer segmentation, and the incrementality and ROI of our Marketing dollars
Spearhead proper experiment design, and provide advanced analytical support on A/B tests with clear conclusions on test outcomes
Partner with business leads and Hims leadership to identify new reporting and data requirements, document requirements, build reports and coordinate with engineering to provide the necessary data points
Monitor website traffic and conversion metrics, customer engagement levels and LTVs on an ongoing basis. Be the subject matter expert on identifying overall trends and diagnosing data anomalies
Experience & Skills:
8+ years of in-depth Business Intelligence experience ideally in partnership with Marketing, Live Ops, Growth, or Product Management departments
Strong communication skills. Able to effectively communicate in a clear and concise manner. Experience communicating analyses and fielding questions from executive team members
Experience with experiment design and A/B test analysis across multiple KPIs
Ability to think through complex problems, determine proper analytical processes and procedures, independently derive conclusions and present results to the team
Detail-oriented and exceptionally organized. Able to multi-task, prioritize, and manage multiple projects in a fast-paced, ambiguous environment
Experience with cross team project management
Expert proficiency with SQL
Experience with Web Analytics platforms (Amplitude a huge plus)
Experience with data visualization software (Tableau Desktop or Looker is a plus)
Experience with BigQuery/Snowflake and Python a plus
We are focused on building a diverse and inclusive workforce. If you're excited about this role, but do not meet 100% of the qualifications listed above, we encourage you to apply.
